## Architecture

```
React SPA  ──REST──►  FastAPI  ──HTTPS──►  Anthropic Claude API
```

The frontend handles everything — quiz scoring, chart animation, simulation — entirely client-side. The backend only gets called for Monte Carlo, AI debrief, and auth.

**Fallbacks:**
- Monte Carlo: client-side JS fallback using the same Box-Muller algorithm
- Debrief: pre-authored (profile × decision) matrix if Claude API is unavailable
- API key is never in the client bundle — all Anthropic calls go through the backend proxy

### API endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | What it does |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/simulation/{stockId}` | GET | Weekly price series + event annotations |
| `/api/montecarlo` | POST | Runs 1,000 scenarios, returns distribution |
| `/api/debrief` | POST | Calls Claude, returns behavioral analysis JSON |
| `/api/auth/login` | POST | Returns JWT |
| `/api/auth/me` | GET | Validates token, returns user |
| `/api/history` | POST | Saves completed simulation |

### Frontend files

| File | Does what |
|---|---|
| `App.jsx` | State + routing |
| `LandingPage.jsx` | Three entry paths |
| `FearQuizPage.jsx` | Quiz + profile scoring |
| `StockPickerPage.jsx` | Asset selection |
| `SimulatorPage.jsx` | Crash animation + decision modal |
| `LossMeterPage.jsx` | Monte Carlo chart |
| `DebriefPage.jsx` | AI analysis + SIP calculator |
| `MarketsPage.jsx` | Dashboard |
| `LearnPage.jsx` | Glossary + strategy profiles |
| `ProfilePage.jsx` | User history |
| `api.js` | All backend calls |
| `marketData.js` | All historical data, quiz questions, profiles |

